From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PiTv Build <build@pitv>
Date: Wed, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Use qt6_add_shaders instead of versionless qt_add_shaders

ECMQmlModule6.cmake sets QT_NO_CREATE_VERSIONLESS_FUNCTIONS=ON while
calling find_package(Qt6 COMPONENTS Core Qml). This causes Qt6ShaderTools
to be loaded (via the Qml plugin dependency chain) without registering the
versionless qt_add_shaders alias. A subsequent find_package(Qt6 COMPONENTS
ShaderTools) is a no-op because the package is already marked found, so
qt_add_shaders is never defined and cmake errors with "Unknown CMake command".

The versioned qt6_add_shaders is always registered unconditionally, so use
that instead.

Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 src/qmlcontrols/graphicaleffects/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/qmlcontrols/graphicaleffects/CMakeLists.txt b/src/qmlcontrols/graphicaleffects/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/qmlcontrols/graphicaleffects/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/qmlcontrols/graphicaleffects/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@ ecm_add_qml_module(graphicaleffects URI org.kde.graphicaleffects

 ecm_generate_qdoc(graphicaleffects graphicaleffects.qdocconf)

-qt_add_shaders(graphicaleffects "graphicaleffects_shaders"
+qt6_add_shaders(graphicaleffects "graphicaleffects_shaders"
     BATCHABLE
     PRECOMPILE
     OPTIMIZED
